##  Industry Interaction Reflection

From industry-related discussions and learning, I understood how professional environments operate in real-world IT settings.

**What I Learned:**  
Industry professionals emphasized the importance of both technical expertise and soft skills such as communication, teamwork, and problem-solving.

**New Insights:**  
- Real-world software development is collaborative and deadline-driven  
- Continuous learning is essential due to evolving technologies  
- Practical experience is highly valued in the industry  

**Skills Required in Real-World Jobs:**  
- Programming and analytical thinking  
- Communication and teamwork  
- Version control systems (Git/GitHub)  
- Adaptability to modern tools and technologies  

